title: Supermodel Linda Evangelista Says Cosmetic Procedure Left Her ‘Disfigured’
content: The ’90s-era supermodel said side effects from a fat-freezing procedure caused her to become depressed and turned her into a recluse after “not looking like myself any longer.”

title: ‘The Most Beautiful Boy in the World’ Review: A Cautionary Tale
content: The 1971 film “Death in Venice” showcased the delicate androgyny of Bjorn Andresen’s face and form, but the changes it wrought on his life are indelible.

title: Valentino Wants Everyone to Get Vaxxed — and Cloned
content: How an upstart label joined forces with the Italian luxury brand to create some very of-the-moment sweats.

title: Thousands Evacuated as Canary Island Volcano Erupts
content: A volcano on the island of La Palma spewed lava and smoke, prompting an evacuation of thousands and forcing the Spanish prime minister to delay a trip to New York.

title: Residents of Troubled Supertall Tower Seek $125 Million in Damages
content: The condo board at 432 Park Avenue is suing the developers for construction and design defects that have led to floods, faulty elevators, and electrical explosions.

title: Republican Review of Arizona Vote Fails to Show Stolen Election
content: The much criticized review showed much the same results as in November, with 99 more Biden votes and 261 fewer Trump ones.

title: Does My Mask Protect Me if Nobody Else Is Wearing One?
content: Masks work best when everyone in the room has one on, but you’ll still benefit from masking up even when those around you aren’t.

title: Gwen Ifill Was Right About ‘Missing White Woman Syndrome’
content: I’ve seen it happen time and again. Missing white women and girls receive outsize media coverage when other missing people receive none.
